{\b0 \cf25 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\b0 \cf25 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\b0 \cf25 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
Complaint was filed seeking declaratory and injunctive relief against proposed expansion of motel. The Circuit Court for Monroe County, J. Jefferson Overby, J., upheld issuance of building permit, and appeal was taken. The District Court of Appeal, 
}
{\field {\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://www.westlaw.com/Link/Document/FullText?findType=h&pubNum=176284&cite=0141887401&originatingDoc=I1101afc40dc211d99830b5efa1ded32a&refType=RQ&originationContext=document&vr=3.0&rs=cblt1.0&transitionType=DocumentItem&contextData=(sc.CustomDigest)" }{\fldrslt 
{\b0 \cf30 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
Schwartz
}}}
{\b0 \cf25 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
, C.J., held that motel had been a grandfathered nonconforming use since county had first enacted a zoning ordinance and therefore could not be treated as if it were in a district permitting motel usage and subsequent expansion.
\par 
}
}
}
{\b0 \cf25 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
\u160\'3f
\par 
}
{\b0 \cf25 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\b0 \cf25 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\b0 \cf25 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
Reversed with directions.
\par 
}
}
}
{\b0 \cf25 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
\u160\'3f
\par 
}
}
{\b0 \cf25 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\b1 \cf25 \f2 \i0 \fs20 
{\b1 \cf25 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
Procedural Posture(s):
}
}
{\b0 \cf25 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 On Appeal.
\par 
}
}
