The trial court ultimately concluded that Dowd had mistakenly filed a complaint for declaratory and injunctive relief and that certiorari was the appropriate remedy instead. We agree that the County Commission\rquote s approval of the building permit, which involved only a legal question of its validity 
}
{\b0 \cf1 \f5 \i1 \fs20 
{\b0 \cf1 \f5 \ul0 \strike0 \i1 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
vel non,
}
}
{\b0 \cf1 \f5 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 was not a quasi-judicial determination and was thus appropriately subject to the declaratory relief sought below. 
}
